item.title: Optimizing a function
item.description: In the golang community slack, someone shared a link to a package used to validate Swedish personnumer. Personnumer is a swedish version of an ID, and its format is well defined: First 6 or 8 digits is a birthrate with or without a century. Last four digits are random secret digits. The whole number satisfies the Luhn algorithm. Birthdate and secret digits can be divided with - or +. For example 19900101-0017
